      <titleblock previous-project="column-marble-gambler" next-project="marble-clock">The Henk Slomp objects</titleblock>

      <block layout="text-right">
        <text>
          <p><a href="https://www.henkslomp.nl/" target="_blank">Henk Slomp</a> is a Dutch artist that works with steel and other cool materials. He
            lives and has a gallery at <a
              href="https://www.google.nl/maps/place/14+Rue+Prte+Fouron,+58140+Lormes,+France/@47.2895305,3.8190509,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m5!3m4!1s0x47f1e4150677be81:0xbc6ac40a50095c6d!8m2!3d47.2895305!4d3.8190509"
              target="_blank">Rue Porte Fouron 14, Lormes, France</a> (in the Morvan).</p>
          <p>We met in the summer of 2021, purely by chance. Together we created an installation with steel egg-shaped objects hanging in a space.
            These objects click, light, move and react on where you are in the room.</p>
          <p>You can visit the installation (the gallery is open on Thursdays and Saturdays), walk between the objects and see and hear how they react
            to you. It&#x2019;s a magical experience.</p>
        </text>
